<headline>Fire Warning issued March 29 at 7:13PM CDT  by NWS Amarillo</headline>
<description>The National Weather Service in Amarillo has issued a Fire Warning
at the request of Emergency Management for northwestern Gray County.
* AT 708 PM CDT, a dangerous wildfire was located 3 miles south of
Pampa, moving rapidly east northeast about 3 to 5 mph.
* Areas impacted...Just south of Pampa.
$$
DGW</description>
<instruction>Be prepared to evacuate quickly if requested and follow all safety
instructions from local emergency management officials. Do not drive
into smoke.
Firefighters and incident responders should anticipate extreme fire
behavior including a wind-driven and torching fire.</instruction>
